race.description: Hkjc World Pool Red Anchor Stakes (G3)
race.comment: NAPOLEONIC (2) comes down from Sydney with strong form. She beat subsequent Listed winner Ohope two back in sharp splits at Warwick Farm two starts ago, measuring up well to G2 company last time when fourth. Finds the right race here and McDonald hops back aboard. PRINCE TYCOON (1) resumes. He looked good winning on debut as favourite, perhaps unsuited back to 1000m at Gold Coast thereafter when thought of as a Magic Millions 2yo Classic contender. He's won a jumpout leading in and may well be improved this time around. SNOW MERCY (8) was big odds but won in a driving finish to score the G3 Champagne Stakes here last time out. Not sure that's the strongest form line but she's hard to knock. VIRTUAL ILLUSION (3) is unbeaten in two runs in South Australia and can reel off a big late sectional. ST EDWARD (4) can go on with a solid win here last time.
